    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc_vm.00187.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place" rend="right">Kirkwood <choice><abbr>N.J.</abbr><expan>New Jersey</expan></choice></name>
                    <date when="1878-03-26"><choice><abbr>Mar</abbr><expan>March</expan></choice> 26th. 1878.</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear Walt&#8212;</salute>
            </opener>

            <p>as I have thought of you almost constantly since I came home I thought I would write a few lines to you to let you know that I am feeling pretty well, and <choice><sic>sinceerly</sic><corr>sincerely</corr></choice> hope that you are the same.<ptr target="n0590"/></p>
           
            <p>Mother<ptr target="n1039"/> <gap reason="damage" extent="2 or 3 words" quantity="12" unit="chars"/> day, <gap reason="damage" extent="1 line" quantity="24" unit="chars"/> been <gap reason="damage" extent="1 line" quantity="24" unit="chars"/> she <gap reason="damage" extent="1 line" quantity="15" unit="chars"/> City before <gap reason="damage" extent="4 or 5 words" quantity="15" unit="chars"/> if she should <gap reason="damage" extent="1 words" quantity="6" unit="chars"/> no doubt but that she will stop in to see you on her
            
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc_vm.00188.jpg" type="verso"/>
            
            her <gap reason="damage" extent="2 words" quantity="8" unit="chars"/>. Things are about as they were when you was down here, (any more than we have had a fearful <choice><sic>storme</sic><corr>storm</corr></choice> of wind and sand). The wind blew so hard last Sunday night, that it almost upset me when I was <choice><sic>comeing</sic><corr>coming</corr></choice> home, "for I was <hi rend="underline">out</hi> then, as usual." Father and all are well: "John" the 'darkey man' is here yet: <gap reason="damage" extent="1 word" quantity="7" unit="chars"/> and George have their fun <gap reason="damage" extent="3 or 4 words" quantity="12" unit="chars"/> has been <gap reason="damage" extent="1 line" quantity="20" unit="chars"/> the <gap reason="damage" extent="2 lines" quantity="30" unit="chars"/> has been <gap reason="damage" extent="4 or 5 words" quantity="15" unit="chars"/> about drinking it to <gap reason="damage" extent="1 word" quantity="10" unit="chars"/> his skin white; it rather gets to him, but he takes it all in good
            
            <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="loc_vm.00189.jpg" type="recto"/>
            
            part: he asked Van<ptr target="n0883"/> <gap reason="damage" extent="1 words" quantity="5" unit="chars"/> other day, <choice><sic>wheather</sic><corr>whether</corr></choice> the first man on earth was black or white, and Van told him the first man was white, and then John asked him where the black man came from, and Van told <choice><sic>hime</sic><corr>him</corr></choice> that a black man was a monkey with his tail cut off, so he gave up talking to him and <choice><sic>whent</sic><corr>went</corr></choice> on with <choice><sic>Georg</sic><corr>George</corr></choice>.</p> <p>There is quite <gap reason="damage" extent="2 words" quantity="5" unit="chars"/> in the music since <gap reason="damage" extent="3 words" quantity="8" unit="chars"/> the wind is <gap reason="damage" extent="3 lines" quantity="60" unit="chars"/> "Age of <gap reason="damage" extent="1 line" quantity="20" unit="chars"/> wish you <gap reason="damage" extent="3 or 4 words" quantity="12" unit="chars"/>, I have been going <gap reason="damage" extent="2 or 3 words" quantity="8" unit="chars"/> for it for sometime but haven't thought of it before.</p>
            
            <pb xml:id="leaf002v" facs="loc_vm.00190.jpg" type="verso"/>
            
            <p>I have been thinking of the suit of <choice><orig>cloths</orig><reg>clothes</reg></choice> which I am to have like yours: I have had myself all pictured out with a suit of gray, and a white slouch hat on about fifty times, since you spoke of it; the fellows will call me Walt then. I will have to do something great and good in honor of the name. What will it be? <gap reason="damage" extent="4 or 5 words" quantity="15" unit="chars"/> have to close, <gap reason="damage" extent="1 line" quantity="20" unit="chars"/> out <gap reason="damage" extent="1 line" quantity="20" unit="chars"/> at <gap reason="damage" extent="1 line" quantity="20" unit="chars"/> Friday <gap reason="damage" extent="1 line" quantity="20" unit="chars"/></p>
            
            <closer>
                <salute>Yours truly</salute>
                <signed>Harry Stafford</signed>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
                <p>PS. write soon and let know how you are Yours H.S.</p>
            </postscript>
        </body>
